  "body": "This is a code/feature request:\r\n\r\nCurrently adding a new table requires modifying table.go in erigon-lib, adding a constant to ChainDataTables array.\r\n\r\nProblem: I'm doing some tests with new indexes, had to fork erigon-lib and replace the version in go.mod@erigon. Having to rebase it every new release is driving me crazy, pls I need a solution üòõ\r\n\r\nIs there some workaround that could be coded so I don't have to change erigon-lib, but also keep whatever safety checkings erigon does at init?\r\n\r\nMy tables have a \"Ots_\" name prefix if this could help in any way. I can change the prefix to something more neutral if you can go with having a standard prefix for custom tables.",
